article.headline: Wolf Pack earn shot at UConn
article.story: RENO, Nev. (AP) -- Junior guard Kirk Snyder scored 17 points and senior forward Todd Okeson added 11 points and nine assists Monday as Nevada beat Vermont 69-49 in the first round of the Preseason NIT. The Wolf Pack (1-0) built a 41-22 halftime lead on the strength of a 26-4 run that lasted nearly 11 minutes. The rest of the way the Catamounts (0-1) never got closer than 16 points, at 58-42 with 7:46 to play. Vermont was outrebounded 41-28 and had only 15 assists compared to 20 from Nevada, which also forced 18 turnovers. Taylor Coppenrath, the 2003 player of the year in the America East Conference, led all scorers with 17 and was the only Catamount in double figures. Nevada will travel to No. 1 Connecticut for a second-round game Wednesday.
